```julia
function clean_column(col)
    return lowercase(strip(replace(col, r"\s|-", "_")))
end
```
This function first calls the `lowercase` method to convert all characters in the input column name to lowercase. Then it uses the `strip` method to remove any leading or trailing whitespaces from the string. Finally, it uses a regular expression with the `replace` method to replace any spaces and hyphens with an underscore. The resulting string is then returned as the cleaned column name.
